    <div class="intro">
        <h2>Welcome to the Roving Reactor Project</h2>
        <p>The <b>Roving Reactor</b> is an ambitious traveling exhibit designed to bring nuclear energy education directly to the public. We aim to reach thousands of visitors and spark meaningful conversations at events like SXSW, the Daytona 500, and the Minnesota State Fair.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="horizontal-line"></div>
    <div class="intro">
        <h3>Why Nuclear and Microreactors?</h3>
        <p>Nuclear energy, particularly through microreactors, has the potential to provide clean, reliable, and scalable power solutions for a sustainable future. With a unique focus on nuclear batteries, the Roving Reactor highlights how these compact reactors can deliver consistent energy, bridging gaps left by intermittent sources like solar and wind.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="horizontal-line"></div>
    <div class="intro">
        <h3>Key Features of the Exhibit</h3>
        <p>Our exhibit combines immersive, interactive displays and engaging storytelling to make nuclear energy accessible and exciting. A full-size model of a nuclear battery will be at the exhibit's heart, accompanied by hands-on activities that demonstrate the technologyâ€™s potential in everyday life.</p>
    </div>
